column2: How well does text in the slide preserve the key content of the source text?
column3: How well does the generated image help with comprehending the source text?
column4: How well does the text in the slide deck flow in a logical, coherent manner, effectively telling a complete and connected story across the slides?
column5: How well does the sequence of images in the slide deck flow in a logical, coherent manner, effectively telling a complete and connected story across the slides?

column6: the differing art styles or such between images kind of throw me off sometimes (aka. from a realistic image to an illustrated image), which resulted in me giving a lower rating due to coherency (instead of 4 or 5).
The grammar isn’t the best, but it’s okay.
